CONFIRMED genuine skip (#3) — needs the removed embedded-Python interpreter.

use-rs274.cc compiles an external C++ program that embeds the interpreter's
Python-remap support: it `#include <Python.h>` (must be first header) and links
$PYTHON_CPPFLAGS/$PYTHON_LIBS, because the old interp headers exposed Python types
(e.g. `struct inttab`) in the public API. gomc removed the embedded Python
interpreter, so Python.h / $PYTHON_LIBS are not part of the build and rs274ngc.hh
no longer carries Python types — the program cannot be compiled.

Note: the general capability "compile+link an external program against the control
API" still exists and is exercised by build/ui (a C client linked against libgmi).
This test is specifically the Python-embedding compile, which is gone.
